evidence: sending a sequence of pulses toward a target
echo returns with the same amplitude and phase
amplitudes and phases change from pulse to pulse

concepts.term: Imagine you're sending a sequence of pulses toward a target that is not moving. You send one pulse, two pulses, three pulses-each time the echo returns with the same amplitude and phase. If you line up all these received echoes at the same gated time instant, they all align perfectly. The phase remains constant, meaning the surface is stationary.
